[src:sbom/dependency-hell] solves this problem with a concept called slotting, which allows multiple versions of shared libraries to be installed.
[src:sbom/dependency-hell] can perform smart upgrades, in which interdependent software components are upgraded at the same time, thereby resolving the major number incompatibility issue too.
