[src:sbom/dependency-hell] While this does not alleviate the multitude of dependency, it does make the jobs of package managers or installers much easier.
[src:sbom/dependency-hell] A software appliance encapsulates dependencies in a pre-integrated self-contained unit such that users no longer have to worry about resolving software dependencies.
[src:sbom/dependency-hell] Instead the burden is shifted to developers of the software appliance.
[src:sbom/dependency-hell] and Docker Hub) can be seen as an implementation of software appliances.
[src:sbom/dependency-hell] An application (or version of an existing conventional application) that is completely self-contained and requires nothing to be already installed.
[src:sbom/dependency-hell] It is coded to have all necessary components included, or is designed to keep all necessary files within its own directory, and will not create a dependency problem.
[src:sbom/dependency-hell] These are often able to run independently of the system to which they are connected.
[src:sbom/dependency-hell] , which work in much the same way: programs and their dependencies are self-contained in their own directories (folders).
